Quote: Every smoko time . . .[they] would pull their bombs out of snooker and brew up a cup of tea or cocoa. <i>Ibid.</i>148 He had a secret compartment in his slot where he hid all his goods, ... and a couple of screws swooped on [his] place and sprung his snooker. <i>Ibid.</i>249 HEAVY SNOOKER (adj) Well hidden, secret. See SNOOKER. <i>Ibid.</i> 254 SNOOKER (n) and (v) Hide, hiding place. From the term in billiards.
